On Thu, Oct 07, 1999 at 02:47:45PM +0530, CHANDRIKA H V wrote:
> 	*(int *)0 = 0 ;
> 
> 	What is the meaning/significance  of this ?
This is a normal way of causing an Oops.  It gets you a stack backtrace and
register dump which may help you find the cause of the problem.
